1
00:00:01,520 --> 00:00:06,240
THIS DRAMA IS CREATED
FOR ENTERTAINMENT PURPOSES

2
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:10,800
ALL CHARACTERS, SETTINGS
AND EVENTS ARE ENTIRELY FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:15,920
THERE IS NO INTENT TO REFERENCE
ANY ORGANIZATIONS OR INDIVIDUALS

4
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,400
Right now, we can't trust anyone.

5
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,240
If anyone else finds out who we are,

6
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:18,040
it means we're all dead.

7
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:21,160
If you want to destroy
Natee's human trafficking network,

8
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,400
you don't have much time.

9
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:25,960
<i>Is he the special guest</i>
<i>you mentioned, Napa?</i>

10
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,600
<i>He's a newly rich rising tycoon.</i>

11
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:28,640
That's serious money.

12
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:30,960
There's an order to heighten security,

13
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:33,120
especially for Natee's auction tonight.

14
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:36,680
Besides Jack,
there are other dangerous people too?

15
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:38,280
This job's easy.

16
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,400
You noobs.

17
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:41,080
Easy my ass.

18
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:42,080
We're screwed.

19
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:44,720
Sorry, bro. Secrets are out.

20
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:11,400
It's out here in the middle of nowhere.

21
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:14,240
No wonder no one can find the place.

22
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:22,240
- It's not too late, right?
- Not at all.

23
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:24,360
Other guests just went in a moment ago.

24
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:28,160
- Here you go.
- Oh, I'll do it myself.

25
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:30,840
Excuse me, sir.
You'll need to wear a mask.

26
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,800
They're really awful.

27
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:37,080
Everyone has to wear a mask

28
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:40,280
so no one knows customers' identities.

29
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:42,760
You need to be careful.

30
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:44,840
Yeah. Let's go.

31
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,480
Please go ahead.

32
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:48,520
Ah, wait a second. Sorry.

33
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,520
Only one person
is allowed inside, sir. No guards.

34
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:56,600
So I really can't go in?

35
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:58,240
- No, sir.
- Ah, all right.

36
00:04:58,320 --> 00:05:00,120
Sir, please come this way for a moment.

37
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:02,680
Just a moment. Just a moment.

38
00:05:06,760 --> 00:05:09,720
This is insane.
You're going in alone like this?

39
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,520
How are you supposed to get the women out?

40
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:13,760
You've got to find a way
to get me in too. Got it?

41
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:16,040
I'm not some immortal emperor.

42
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:18,920
Look. How am I supposed to bring you in?

43
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,360
There's nothing to do.

44
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,960
I already ordered Sarge
to suspend the mission.

45
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:28,520
They've increased security,

46
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:31,400
set up patrol units
around the auction site.

47
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,520
Didn't he relay the order?

48
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:40,240
- What is it, Sarge?
<i>- Hey.</i>

49
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:43,840
Stop messing with my team. I'm working.

50
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:46,320
Sarge, this mission puts us
at a complete disadvantage.

51
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:49,640
They know. They've activated defenses.
And they've started hunting us.

52
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:51,400
<i>Why are you only thinking about yourself?</i>

53
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,440
Those women are in danger
and need rescue, all right?

54
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:56,520
If you keep talking
like some nagging housewife,

55
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:59,600
I'll crush your lips with mine,

56
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:02,840
<i>kiss you until you can't breathe,</i>
<i>until you can't even talk. Want that?</i>

57
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,520
Damn it, Sarge.

58
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:07,880
If you don't want
these killer lips crushing yours,

59
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:09,400
then stay quiet and trust me.

60
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,640
<i>I won't let this mission fail.</i>

61
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:16,200
Sarge was badass. He really is my idol.
He's going to kiss her.

62
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:22,000
Ms. Duangnet, Natee has arrived.
There's no time left to think.

63
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,320
Fine.

64
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,600
We'll go with Sarge's plan.

65
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:29,320
Moh, hold position outside.

66
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:32,000
Tangkuay and I will enter the auction.

67
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,560
Everything's okay, bro.

68
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:50,760
Please.

69
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:57,920
Boss ordered me
to observe this auction as well.

70
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,680
Suit yourself.

71
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:05,520
But if this auction goes smoothly,
I'll make a lot of money for Boss.

72
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,280
And more importantly,

73
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,280
if I uncover
whoever's been stirring trouble,

74
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:12,600
don't you dare take credit for it.

75
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:24,240
The auction's about to start.
Check all items.

76
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:25,600
Yes, sir.

77
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:43,960
Hey, open the door.

78
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:51,840
Move. Back off.

79
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:56,920
Hey, hey, don't.

80
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:04,920
Hey. Come here.

81
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,920
- Go!
- Come here. Go!

82
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,520
Come here. Move.

83
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,440
Come with me.

84
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:20,520
- Or do you want to die? Come with me.
- Let me go. No.

85
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:25,480
Okay, roger that.

86
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:32,520
Man, I really want
something cold to drink.

87
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:37,200
Excuse me, do you have something like…

88
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:40,919
Something that hits the throat?

89
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,640
What do you mean? Hits the throat?

90
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:44,760
Like… Something that…

91
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:47,240
- What are you doing?
- You guys are next.

92
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:56,040
Come on. Come on.

93
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:09,600
Juk.

94
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,680
- Stand by to take out the front line.
- Yes, Sarge.

95
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,640
Akki. Moh.

96
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:14,360
Hold on.

97
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:21,000
- Sup.
- <i>Sarge, when are we moving?</i>

98
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:24,440
What's with you? First you're out,
now you're in a hurry?

99
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:28,000
I've found all the women they took.
And the auction is about to begin.

100
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:30,240
I know. That's why I told you to trust me.

101
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:34,200
How am I supposed to trust you?
You haven't told me the plan at all.

102
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:36,760
<i>Then don't trust me.</i>
<i>Just play along. I promise</i>

103
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,800
it'll be thrilling. And fun. That's it.

104
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,120
You idiot.

105
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:46,120
Where were we?

106
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:49,040
I think we should start over, Sarge.

107
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:50,680
Then we start over.

108
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:54,800
- Juk.
- What now, Sarge?

109
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,360
Go.

110
00:09:58,840 --> 00:09:59,760
Juk.

111
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,440
- Stand by to take out the front line.
- Yes, Sarge.

112
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:03,640
Akki. Moh. Go support Tangkuay.

113
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:05,120
- Yes, Sarge.
- Kla, you're with me.

114
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,080
Yes, Sarge.

115
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,200
Go.

116
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:08,160
Wait.

117
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,720
Nothing. Let's go.

118
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:20,040
I swear, Sarge's losing it
more and more every day.

119
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:42,800
Distinguished gentlemen,

120
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:45,600
this is our first item.

121
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:46,560
Excellent structure.

122
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:49,600
Fresh internal organs, guaranteed.

123
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:52,960
And most importantly, disease-free.

124
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:55,120
Whoever gets it, I guarantee

125
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,120
it's worth every single cent.

126
00:10:58,120 --> 00:10:59,480
If everyone is ready,

127
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,240
you may begin bidding.

128
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:09,280
Hey, wait. Where are you going?

129
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:12,560
Hello. We're delivering fruit.

130
00:11:13,160 --> 00:11:14,640
Where's your fruit?

131
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:19,080
Right here. Seedless sugar apples.

132
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:22,160
It's time to go to war
and smash the first pillar, guys!

133
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:23,320
Take this!

134
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:27,240
- Hey.
- Hey.

135
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:29,560
What's happening?

136
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:33,480
Hey.

137
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:35,760
Go.

138
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,560
Let's go.

139
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:03,040
- Go now.
- Go.

140
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:24,680
Hey.

141
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:31,760
Hey!

142
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,760
So? Was the sugar apple good?

143
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:48,880
Hey.

144
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:06,120
Hey, what?

145
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,760
Stay still.
Move and I'll blow your guts out.

146
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:10,360
Stay still.

147
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,720
Go. Go.

148
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:24,240
We're here, assholes!

149
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:32,800
- Yeah! Woohoo!
- Yeah.

150
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:35,320
Hey!

151
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:37,760
What the hell?

152
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:40,000
Come on.

153
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:45,520
- Damn, we're freaking awesome.
- This is so fire, bro.

154
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,280
Yeah. But for now, let's split up.

155
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:48,520
- Why?
- Back's starting to hurt.

156
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:51,560
- Come on.
- Come on.

157
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:54,040
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

158
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,880
- Whoa, hey.
- Whoop. Hey.

159
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:00,800
- Hey.
- Boss.

160
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:02,840
Who did this?

161
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:04,480
No idea, sir. They screwed with us.

162
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:07,000
How could you not know?
You've got so many people.

163
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:09,320
They messed me up this badly.
Go find them! Go!

164
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:10,680
Let's go.

165
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:23,080
Hey.

166
00:14:23,680 --> 00:14:24,480
- Hurry.
- Go.

167
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,680
I'm here to help you. Hurry, get out.

168
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:40,440
- Hurry.
- Hurry, get out.

169
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:42,200
- Hey, hurry.
- Hurry.

170
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:47,200
Hey.

171
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:48,640
- Take cover.
- Go.

172
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:53,640
Hey.

173
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,920
- Go, go.
- Hurry. Get up. Hurry.

174
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:34,560
Kla, enough. Go.

175
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:48,280
How's Mom?

176
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:51,400
Same as always.

177
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,760
Dad, just admit

178
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:02,520
that you didn't actually come
to visit Mom.

179
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:08,920
My men said the person you hit

180
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,400
already left the hospital.

181
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:13,720
It's like he knew
my men were watching him.

182
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:16,640
Dad.

183
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:18,920
When are you going to stop doing this?

184
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,760
When I'm sure.

185
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,600
I already know.

186
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:27,080
His brother came
and took him out of the hospital.

187
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:30,760
Right now, I don't trust anyone
to be near you.

188
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:34,920
But the more you forbid it,

189
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:37,840
the more interested I get.

190
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:40,640
He does seem intriguing.

191
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,440
Maybe…

192
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:45,800
I want to develop
our relationship further.

193
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:48,760
How far are you going to
spite me like this, Mook?

194
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:56,720
What did you say?

195
00:16:58,680 --> 00:16:59,680
Who did it?

196
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:03,840
What did you say? The women escaped?

197
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:06,319
Damn it. What am I supposed to do now?

198
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:11,800
Shit.

199
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:45,960
I've got nothing against you.

200
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:48,120
I'm just following Boss's orders.

201
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:50,480
You can explain yourself to him later.

202
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:37,720
Sarge, how's everyone?

203
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:41,480
Everyone's safe. Mission accomplished.

204
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:44,680
- These two?
- We'll talk later.

205
00:18:45,480 --> 00:18:48,040
Without them,
this job wouldn't have been done.

206
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:51,760
Where's my sister?

207
00:18:57,120 --> 00:18:57,960
Napa.

208
00:18:58,040 --> 00:18:59,120
Nid.

209
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:04,160
How are you?

210
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:06,800
See? I told you to trust me.

211
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,720
Thrilling. Fun.

212
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:11,320
Still want that crushing kiss?

213
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:16,080
Thank you, Mr. Kla.

214
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:18,960
Now I really believe
your amulet is sacred.

215
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:21,320
That's why the mission succeeded.

216
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:25,360
But I'll return it to you,
so it can protect you.

217
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:28,200
Mr. Kla.

218
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:29,120
- Mr. Kla.
- Hey, Kla.

219
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,120
- Kla.
- Kla, what's wrong?

220
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:31,520
- Kla.
- Kla.

221
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,560
Did you get shot?

222
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:33,920
Nothing, Sarge. Just an ant bite.

223
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,280
Ant bite? There's so much blood.

224
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:37,720
Get him to the safe house.
I'll bring a doctor.

225
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:40,560
I'll move the women to a safe place.

226
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:42,240
They'll be witnesses for the case.

227
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:43,840
- Go.
- Everyone, take Kla first.

228
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:44,800
- Kla, come on.
- Careful.

229
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:45,960
- Come on.
- I'll watch your back.

230
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:47,240
- Watch the wound. Get in the car.
- Come.

231
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:48,200
Go, Kla. Hurry.

232
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:50,280
Get in the car.

233
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:04,440
Damn it, Kla. Your amulet's fake
from a hundred meters away.

234
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:06,280
Got shot and still claimed you were tough.

235
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:09,680
Hey.

236
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:13,880
<i>Sarge, what happened?</i>

237
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:16,840
More of them are coming.
You go. I've got this.

238
00:20:25,520 --> 00:20:26,840
Hey!

239
00:20:29,360 --> 00:20:30,440
Boo!

240
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:47,320
Hey.

241
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:55,960
No accidents since I bought it.
What a waste. Damn you guys.

242
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:03,680
It hurts!

243
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:10,840
- You twisted me like a steering wheel!
- Yeah.

244
00:21:31,680 --> 00:21:32,840
Grenade! Ah!

245
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:51,560
Who's that?

246
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,720
Hey, why are you posing like that?

247
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:58,520
What's wrong with you?

248
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:01,280
You're a Manchester United fan?

249
00:22:01,360 --> 00:22:03,360
Kicking hard again. And again.

250
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:05,240
Whoa. Hey.

251
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:15,520
How's that? Your hand hurts now?

252
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:17,680
Next you'll get a header like Mbappé.

253
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:24,040
Then the Barcelona charging bull.

254
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:25,360
Hey.

255
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,120
Hey.

256
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:44,600
So you wanna do it like this?

257
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:47,480
If you want it, I'll give it to you.

258
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:26,560
You're damn lucky.

259
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:28,120
You get to see my trick shot.

260
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:30,560
Meet Dab the Red Inferno!

261
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:33,560
What Red Inferno? Football?

262
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:54,360
What kind of bullet is this?

263
00:23:57,080 --> 00:23:58,120
Damn it.

264
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:01,200
Huh.

265
00:24:01,760 --> 00:24:05,160
Thought you were tough. You ran off
with your tail between your legs.

266
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:08,240
Sarge.

267
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:09,760
What are you guys doing here?

268
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:12,280
Ms. Duangnet said you were being hunted.

269
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:16,720
But you were insanely cool.

270
00:24:16,800 --> 00:24:20,400
What a shot. Bang, bang.
How did you do that?

271
00:24:21,280 --> 00:24:24,280
Count yourselves lucky.
I'll tell you later.

272
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:26,640
Then why didn't you chase them?

273
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:29,800
My pants got stuck.

274
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:34,000
Gentle please.

275
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:39,640
Hang in there, man.

276
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:42,840
Is it really bad, Napa?

277
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:44,600
Yeah.

278
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:46,400
I can only stop the bleeding temporarily.

279
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:50,400
Hang in there.
Ms. Duangnet said she's bringing a doctor.

280
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,360
- Mr. Kla.
- Ms. Khim.

281
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:55,120
Don't worry.

282
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:57,520
Thank you so much, Ms. Khim.

283
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:05,360
Mr. Kla.

284
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:14,880
Kla.

285
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:21,120
Mr. Kla.

286
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:22,720
Is he dead?

287
00:25:24,520 --> 00:25:26,960
So now Seven Legends are down to six.

288
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:31,760
Rest in peace, my friend.

289
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:36,200
He's not dead.

290
00:25:41,320 --> 00:25:42,160
Just unconscious.

291
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:45,200
Oh. Just unconscious.

292
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:46,120
Phew.

293
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:50,480
Whoa, hey, hey. What is going on?
Hey, back up. Move. You're in the way.

294
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:51,880
Hey. Hey. Hey. What's wrong?

295
00:25:51,960 --> 00:25:55,160
Hey, let me see. Here. Kid, right here.

296
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:56,520
Press the wound. Let me see.

297
00:25:56,600 --> 00:25:59,560
Open up. Damn. Oh shit.

298
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,920
I'm telling you,
if we don't remove the bullet fast,

299
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,920
your loverboy is dead for sure.

300
00:26:04,440 --> 00:26:05,480
Wait a second, Auntie.

301
00:26:05,560 --> 00:26:07,360
- Are you really a doctor?
- Keep pressing it.

302
00:26:07,440 --> 00:26:09,040
Talk to me first, Auntie.

303
00:26:09,120 --> 00:26:10,680
- What?
- You're really a doctor, right?

304
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:13,200
Damn right. If you guys
can go on undercover missions,

305
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:16,400
why can't I be
an undercover doctor selling pad thai?

306
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:17,920
Hey.

307
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:20,680
Shit. This is bad.

308
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:23,760
It's serious.
I think I can't handle it alone.

309
00:26:23,840 --> 00:26:24,840
What do I do?

310
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:26,680
I used to be a nurse.

311
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:29,120
A nurse? Good.

312
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:30,920
You, stay here. Keep pressure on it.

313
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,880
You, get out. And you too.

314
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:34,600
- You talk too much. Get out!
- Uh. Please.

315
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:36,240
- Please take care of my friend.
- Yeah.

316
00:26:36,760 --> 00:26:38,240
- Here. Come on.
- I've put in on already.

317
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:40,960
Yeah, and they're contaminated.
Don't you see?

318
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:42,840
Don't die yet, kid!

319
00:26:42,920 --> 00:26:44,040
Screw it.

320
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:47,960
Stuff it into the hole. Yeah.
Then stitch it.

321
00:26:58,640 --> 00:27:00,360
Is he okay, Doctor?

322
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:02,400
Barely.

323
00:27:02,480 --> 00:27:06,320
If we were any later,
there would've been a loss.

324
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:11,120
I really want to know
which one of those pigs

325
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:13,320
gathered a bunch of screwups

326
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:16,440
to run a suicide mission like this.

327
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:20,240
- It's my dad.
- huh?

328
00:27:22,240 --> 00:27:23,600
Director Pantong?

329
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:26,680
No wonder.

330
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:30,600
Director Pantong really has sharp eyes.

331
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:33,480
He saw something good in these guys.

332
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:37,040
Guess my eyes
weren't good enough to see it.

333
00:27:37,120 --> 00:27:38,840
We're all like you, Doctor.

334
00:27:40,120 --> 00:27:42,160
If you're good,
you don't need to show off.

335
00:27:42,240 --> 00:27:44,880
Look at you. Perfect disguise.

336
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:47,280
Sarge, she far outranks you.

337
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:49,320
Oh really?

338
00:27:50,280 --> 00:27:51,160
Yeah.

339
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:52,720
She's the only remaining backup.

340
00:27:52,800 --> 00:27:54,960
For emergency support.

341
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:59,120
With a mouth like that,
if something happens to him,

342
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:00,480
don't help him.

343
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:02,640
Waste of time. He's just a burden.

344
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:04,640
Hey.

345
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:08,840
But today's mission went smoothly
because of me, right?

346
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:11,000
Working without a plan.

347
00:28:11,080 --> 00:28:13,800
No respect for the chain of command.
Always improvising.

348
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:16,120
If anyone dies, I'll hold you responsible.

349
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:17,680
Hey, wait.

350
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:20,760
If you're going to fight, I'm out.

351
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:22,360
- No, Doctor.
- No, Doctor.

352
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:24,400
Just kidding.

353
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:28,320
- I'm joking. Damn it.
- Yes.

354
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:35,520
If there's an emergency, same as always.

355
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:37,720
Cook-to-order food.

356
00:28:39,800 --> 00:28:40,640
I'll come right away.

357
00:28:43,880 --> 00:28:44,720
Let's go.

358
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:49,560
Hey.

359
00:28:50,880 --> 00:28:52,920
He's mouthy,

360
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:56,760
but I bet he's insanely hot.

361
00:28:56,840 --> 00:29:00,680
He's handsome and buff.

362
00:29:00,760 --> 00:29:03,240
If you're lonely, go for it.

363
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:10,200
Are you talking about me? What hot?

364
00:29:10,280 --> 00:29:13,360
What's wrong with you, fuzz-top?

365
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:15,320
Eavesdropping on people.

366
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:16,440
I said,

367
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:19,560
"Is this your car? it looks good."

368
00:29:19,640 --> 00:29:22,320
You're unbelievable!

369
00:29:23,320 --> 00:29:25,120
I'm going. I'm leaving!

370
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,800
- Are you going back to base?
- What now?

371
00:29:31,640 --> 00:29:32,560
This is base.

372
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:35,880
Just checking if I forgot anything.

373
00:29:35,960 --> 00:29:37,720
I'm not going in then. Ugh!

374
00:29:37,800 --> 00:29:39,840
- Damn you.
- Forgot something or just lost?

375
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:41,400
What a busybody.

376
00:29:45,800 --> 00:29:46,800
Hey.

377
00:29:48,840 --> 00:29:49,920
Is my hair actually that fuzzy?

378
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:52,880
Yeah.

379
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:54,880
I've been growing it.
Did you talk about me?

380
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:57,360
Don't get ahead of yourself.

381
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:01,960
I'm waiting for today's mission report

382
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:03,920
and info on that mysterious gunman.

383
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:04,880
Hurry up.

384
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:07,400
Yes, ma'am.

385
00:30:23,360 --> 00:30:24,720
That's a good match for me.

386
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:26,760
I like it.

387
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:30,600
<i>I heard from Boss</i>
<i>that he sent you to help.</i>

388
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:34,840
But even someone
as good as you got outplayed.

389
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:37,600
That means the other side is no joke.

390
00:30:40,120 --> 00:30:41,600
We just underestimated them a bit.

391
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:46,520
What happened today
wasn't because they're that skilled,

392
00:30:47,600 --> 00:30:50,200
but because there's a mole in our network.

393
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:52,640
A mole?

394
00:31:07,120 --> 00:31:07,960
<i>Let go!</i>

395
00:31:08,560 --> 00:31:09,600
You know who I am? Let go!

396
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:11,880
I don't care.

397
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:28,280
My arm. My arm.

398
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:32,200
This is nothing
compared to the carelessness

399
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:35,280
that made Boss lose money and reputation.

400
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:42,160
I'm sorry. I tried.

401
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:44,760
I'll kneel at Boss's feet if I have to.

402
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:46,880
I'll drag those bastards out myself!

403
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:50,760
The mess you caused

404
00:31:50,840 --> 00:31:53,400
means you no longer get access to Boss.

405
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:56,800
And about dragging them out.

406
00:31:56,880 --> 00:31:59,080
Your own resort is where the mole is.

407
00:32:00,560 --> 00:32:02,480
No. Impossible. There's no way.

408
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:11,920
Boss gives you 48 hours.

409
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:15,800
Find the mole in your place.

410
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:19,160
When the time's up, you know

411
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:21,120
how useless people are dealt with.

412
00:32:23,800 --> 00:32:25,560
Ah! Let go!

413
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:29,720
I'm sorry!

414
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:33,400
I give up. Please let me go.

415
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:10,600
I'm not waiting for your opinion on this.

416
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:13,200
This plan has to be executed immediately.

417
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:16,880
I know. But we just
poked a sleeping tiger.

418
00:33:16,960 --> 00:33:19,680
We need a solid, systematic counterplan.

419
00:33:19,760 --> 00:33:21,960
Otherwise, he wouldn't send
that gunman after us.

420
00:33:22,560 --> 00:33:26,480
That gunman.
If I meet him again, he won't survive.

421
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:29,080
Look at that.

422
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:32,400
But first, we need to deal with Natee.

423
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:34,280
Sarge.

424
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:38,520
Ms. Khim and Ms. Napa
just got word from the resort.

425
00:33:39,040 --> 00:33:41,440
Natee ordered all staff to report in.

426
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:45,200
Anyone who doesn't show up now
will be suspected as a mole.

427
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:49,560
- See? We have to add fuel on the fire now.
- Yeah.

428
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:52,680
Then let's move.

429
00:33:52,760 --> 00:33:54,160
On it, right now.

430
00:33:58,800 --> 00:33:59,640
Let's go.

431
00:34:01,080 --> 00:34:02,160
Dan.

432
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:09,480
No need to order me, Sarge.
I know what to do.

433
00:34:09,560 --> 00:34:13,199
What you're doing is playing with fire.

434
00:34:13,280 --> 00:34:15,840
You're at higher risk than anyone else.

435
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:20,840
My heart isn't given away easily, Sarge.

436
00:34:22,080 --> 00:34:24,000
Unless it's Ms. Duang.

437
00:34:31,880 --> 00:34:33,520
Let's talk about something else.

438
00:34:35,239 --> 00:34:36,880
But on this, I agree with Sarge.

439
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:39,320
Tiangmon is very protective
of his daughter.

440
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:41,679
The only reason
you're still standing is luck.

441
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:44,679
But if you let Mookda find out
she was being used,

442
00:34:44,760 --> 00:34:46,760
and Tiangmon finds out,

443
00:34:48,280 --> 00:34:49,600
your little Dan

444
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:54,000
will be the first thing Tiangmon cuts down
while you're still conscious.

445
00:34:56,760 --> 00:34:59,360
So if you don't want
your little brother sliced up,

446
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:03,800
get the locations of the call center
and gambling site hideouts from Mookda,

447
00:35:03,880 --> 00:35:05,200
then get out fast.

448
00:35:06,040 --> 00:35:08,760
So we can finally start
taking down their second pillar.

449
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:13,160
Yes, sir and ma'am.

450
00:35:15,080 --> 00:35:16,560
This is very important, Dan.

451
00:35:17,560 --> 00:35:20,280
Even when I went undercover
and earned their trust,

452
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:22,040
they still didn't tell me anything.

453
00:35:32,440 --> 00:35:33,320
Ratee.

454
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:35,360
Take a seat.

455
00:35:40,040 --> 00:35:41,760
You're not seriously hurt, are you?

456
00:35:42,920 --> 00:35:44,560
I almost didn't make it, boss.

457
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:46,520
Gunfire everywhere.
I couldn't tell who was who.

458
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:49,000
So I pulled out and hid until I was sure.

459
00:35:49,080 --> 00:35:52,120
Because besides the people
who infiltrated the auction,

460
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:55,520
I also saw others going after Natee.

461
00:35:56,160 --> 00:35:58,920
They're extremely skilled.
Not ordinary at all.

462
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:01,000
Arab Dammoh

463
00:36:02,720 --> 00:36:05,000
is an assassin Boss trusts.

464
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:07,680
Since Jack died, Boss sent him in to help.

465
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:12,880
I've never heard you mention him.

466
00:36:13,560 --> 00:36:16,040
He's the assassin Boss trusts the most.

467
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:19,840
Besides me, he's one of the few
who's seen Boss in person.

468
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:23,720
So if someone at that level was sent,
that means…

469
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:24,640
Yes.

470
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:28,480
The ones causing trouble for us and Natee

471
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:32,320
are moles working with the government.

472
00:36:32,400 --> 00:36:34,240
Once they were exposed,

473
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:36,240
they tried to blackmail us
with the Death File.

474
00:36:37,160 --> 00:36:39,240
It's the data that can lead to Boss.

475
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:42,400
Death File?

476
00:36:43,440 --> 00:36:45,400
Data that can lead to Boss?

477
00:36:47,600 --> 00:36:49,040
Boss trusted them deeply.

478
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:53,000
That's why they have a lot of info
on the human-trafficking network.

479
00:36:53,560 --> 00:36:54,800
But don't worry.

480
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:57,240
Arab is hunting them down.

481
00:36:57,840 --> 00:37:01,160
There's no way
those backstabbing dogs survive.

482
00:37:08,040 --> 00:37:09,440
I'm really worried about you.

483
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:13,720
The situation isn't good right now.

484
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:16,040
I want the people close to me

485
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:18,320
to stay where I can see them.

486
00:37:21,760 --> 00:37:23,120
Move in with me.

487
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:37,080
- Hey, Moh.
- What's up, Sarge?

488
00:37:37,160 --> 00:37:39,440
Take my call for me. On the right side.

489
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:45,560
Hurry.

490
00:37:48,760 --> 00:37:50,120
- So what now?
- Answer it.

491
00:37:51,600 --> 00:37:52,480
Hello.

492
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:55,200
I have important information
Sarge must know.

493
00:37:56,320 --> 00:37:57,440
Ms. Duangnet,

494
00:37:57,520 --> 00:37:58,840
Sarge's busy right now.

495
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:01,200
He's handling something important.

496
00:38:01,840 --> 00:38:04,960
Tell him this is critical.
Get him on the line now.

497
00:38:05,560 --> 00:38:07,040
Well… He is…

498
00:38:07,120 --> 00:38:08,360
All right. I'll take it.

499
00:38:08,440 --> 00:38:10,400
Before I get yelled at again.

500
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:14,160
- I'll put it on speaker.
- Can't. My speaker's busted.

501
00:38:14,680 --> 00:38:16,480
The sound's as soft
as an ant peeing. Come.

502
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:18,520
Put it right to my ear.

503
00:38:20,440 --> 00:38:22,640
Yes, babe?

504
00:38:23,440 --> 00:38:25,960
<i>Hello, Sarge. Can you talk now?</i>

505
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:31,000
I can talk. Quit nagging so loud.
You'll never get a husband like that.

506
00:38:32,600 --> 00:38:35,000
Stop messing around.
This is life-or-death.

507
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:37,160
You need to know and act fast.

508
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:40,640
So what exactly do you want me to act on?

509
00:38:42,600 --> 00:38:43,480
What?

510
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:46,760
- Death File?
- Yes.

511
00:38:47,400 --> 00:38:51,600
A crucial file that can expose
and rip off Phoenix's mask.

512
00:39:05,640 --> 00:39:08,080
Hand over the Death File,
and the government will protect you.

513
00:39:08,160 --> 00:39:10,160
<i>You'll see my trick shot too.</i>

514
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:13,880
Soon, we probably
won't see each other again.

515
00:39:13,960 --> 00:39:15,240
What do you mean by that?

516
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:24,120
Hey!

517
00:39:24,200 --> 00:39:26,960
If you still can't tell reality
from fiction,

518
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:28,880
you shouldn't be working with us.

519
00:39:28,960 --> 00:39:30,640
- Hey!
- Moh!

520
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:33,000
You think I'm just your lapdog, Sarge?

521
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:35,440
I'm the leader. You're my subordinate.

522
00:39:35,520 --> 00:39:36,840
When I give an order, you follow it.

523
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:40,880
So all those subordinates who died
died because you were selfish, right?

524
00:39:49,960 --> 00:39:50,920
Hey!

525
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:57,320
It got stuck.
It was fine during rehearsal.

526
00:39:57,400 --> 00:39:59,920
Come on. Let's rehearse again.

527
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:00,840
- Hey, Kie.
- Ready?

528
00:40:00,920 --> 00:40:01,760
Take this.

529
